This paper focuses on using machine learning and signal processing techniques to monitor the independent living needs of patients with dementia, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of machine learning algorithms such as Support Vector Machines and Random Decision Forests also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of data from smart meters, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of machine learning algorithms for classification also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the monitoring of patients with dementia, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
